paragraphs: GAT Exam Schedule (Monday January 05, 2026 Morning and Afternoon Session)

Please find attached the exam venue schedules for the GAT, which will be administered on Monday, January 5, 2026, in both morning and afternoon sessions. The schedules cover applicants who registered during the period December 09–30, 2025. The schedule for applicants who registered on December 31, 2025 will be announced separately; their exam will also be conducted on the same date (afternoon session).

All visually impaired candidates are required to take the GAT at the Disability Center, Lab 1 (Main Campus). If your name is mistakenly listed under a different exam room, please report directly to the Disability Center, Lab 1, on the exam day.

paragraphs: Submission of Updated Grade 12 Examination Results
To all regular undergraduate first-year students,

The Ministry of Education has revised the Ethiopian Secondary School Leaving Certificate Examination (ESSLCE) (Grade 12) results for some students in September 2025. As these results are a key criterion for placement into academic programs at the end of the first semester, it is
necessary to update the records accordingly.

Therefore, the Addis Ababa University Office of the Registrar kindly requests all concerned students to submit their updated Grade 12 examination results by completing the Google Form available at the link below:
https://forms.gle/WwBC8cRXi3ss6TtE6
The final deadline for submission is January 5, 2026. Students are advised to ensure that all required information is completed accurately and submitted on time.
Thank you for your cooperation.
Addis Ababa University
Office of the Registrar
